19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 585, is
21 amended to read as follows:
22 Section 585. A. The Commission may deny any application for
23 license, or suspend or revoke a license issued, or impose a fine, in
24 accordance with the provisions of the Administrative Procedures Act,
HB2997 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 Sect ion 250 et seq. of Title 75 of the Oklahoma Statutes. If the
2 applicant or licensee is a used motor vehicle salesperson, the
3 Commission shall in like manner also notify the person, firm,
4 association, corporation or trust with whom associated, or in whose
5 association the applicant or licensee is about to enter. The
6 Commission shall have the power to compel the production of records
7 and papers bearing upon the complaints. The Commission shall have
8 the power to subpoena and bring before it any person in this state,
9 or take testimony of any such person by deposition, with the same
10 fees and mileage and in the same manner as prescribed by law in
11 judicial procedure before courts of the state in civil cases. Any
12 party to the hearing shall have the right to the attendance of
13 witnesses in his behalf upon designating to the Commission the
14 person or persons sought to be subpoenaed. If the Commission shall
15 determine that any licensee is guilty of violation of any of the
16 provisions of this act, the license of the licensee shall be
17 suspended or revoked, or a fine imposed as authorized by this act.
18 B. The Commission may assess a fine not to exceed One Hundred
19 Dollars ($100.00) against a used motor vehicle dealer who:
20 1. Willfully fails to deliver certificates of title to
21 purchasers of used motor vehicles within thirty (30) days of the
22 sale of the vehicles;
23
24
HB2997 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 2. Fails to properly reassign the certificate of title to a
2 used motor vehicle as required by law upon the sale or transfer of
3 ownership of the used motor vehicle;
4 3. Sells an extended insurance warranty to a purchaser, but
5 fails to provide a copy of the warranty to the purchaser or fails to
6 disclose who the third party insurer will be; or
7 4. Delivers a used motor vehicle to a potential purchaser with
8 the intent to sell the vehicle, but does not complete the
9 transaction within fifteen (15) calendar days of the delivery of the
10 used motor vehicle.
11 C. An appeal from the decision of the Commission to suspend or
12 revoke a license or to impose a fine shall be taken in accordance
13 with Article II of the Administrative Procedures Act, Section 308a
14 et seq. of Title 75 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
15 D. Any applicant or licensee who knowingly or willfully makes
16 or causes to be made any false statement of a fact required under
17 the provisions of Section 581 et seq. of this title shall be subject
18 to an administrative fine not to exceed One Ten Thousand Dollars
19 ($1,000.00) ($10,000.00).
20 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 3601.1, as
21 last amended by Section 36, Chapter 29, O.S.L. 2023 (74 O.S. Supp.
22 2025, Section 3601.1), is amended to read as follows:
23 Section 3601.1. A. For purposes of Sections 3601.1 through
24 3603 of this title, the term "employee" means a full-time employee
HB2997 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 or a ny number of part-time employees whose combined weekly hours of
2 employment equal those of a full-time employee, but shall not
3 include temporary employees working on a seasonal basis between May
4 1 and October 31.
5 B. Beginning July 1, 2008, the maximum number of full-time-
6 equivalent employees for each of the following agencies, boards,
7 commissions, departments, or programs shall not exceed the numbers
8 specified in this section, except as may be authorized pursuant to
9 the provisions of Section 3603 of this title.
